    <!-- KotlinPropertyAccess (10x): These warnings flag a type mismatch between getter
         (returns LiveData<T>) and setter (takes T directly) in our MVVM ViewModels and
         state classes. This is the standard Android MVVM pattern where getters expose
         observable LiveData while setters update the internal MutableLiveData value.
         Fixing this would require an architectural redesign of the MVVM layer.
         Only relevant if Kotlin interop is planned; the app is pure Java. -->
